#MEM id=marcus source=/root/yvon/agent-department/CEO/marcus/TOOLS.md
M|marcus|Marcus never accesses Supabase directly. All mem reads and writes go through `/api/settings`.
M|marcus|**Read at ses start:**
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|GET /api/settings?type=mem&agentId=marcus-ceo&ventureId=<activeVentureId>
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|**Write after task completion:**
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|POST /api/settings
M|marcus|Body: { type: "mem", agentId: "marcus-ceo", ventureId: "<id>", key: "<key>", value: "<value>" }
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|**Keys written every ses:**
M|marcus|- `current_status` — always overwrite with current state
M|marcus|- `recent_tasks` — prepend + trim to 5
M|marcus|- `recent_errors` — append + trim to 5
M|marcus|- `recent_discussions` — append + trim to 5
M|marcus|**Keys written only when confirmed:**
M|marcus|- `current_priorities` — only when Stark explicitly revises
M|marcus|- `strategic_goals_q` — only at quarter start or explicit revision
M|marcus|- `open_decisions` — add when deferred, remove when resolved
M|marcus|- `active_brief_date` — update every time a brief is sent
M|marcus|- `board_context` — only when new investor ctx confirmed
M|marcus|Marcus triggers brief generation via the API route — not directly:
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|POST /api/briefing
M|marcus|Body: { ventureId: "<activeVentureId>", type: "morning" }
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|The brief is then emailed via:
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|POST /api/email
M|marcus|Body: { to: "<BRIEFING_EMAIL>", subject: "CEO Brief — <date>", html: "<brief cnt>" }
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|At ses start, load active vtr config:
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|GET /api/vtr?ventureId=<activeVentureId>
M|marcus|```
M|marcus|Returns: `{ name, slug, igHandle, ytChannelId, liProfileUrl, ga4PropertyId, color }`
M|marcus|In the War Room, Marcus receives specialist briefings via `/api/team-chat`. He does not call tools directly — the orchestrator fans out to specialists and passes all briefings to Marcus for synthesis.
M|marcus|| Tool | Purpose | Status |
M|marcus||------|---------|--------|
M|marcus|| Notion MCP | Write strategic decisions to a company wiki | Planned |
M|marcus|| Slack MCP | Post daily brief summary to a channel | Planned |